# <!-- PROJECT_NAME -->

Requirements Engineering project using the [AI-Augmented RE framework](https://github.com/axelburkhardt/ai-augmented-re).

See `AGENTS.md` for active phase, pipeline status, and AI rules.

## RE Pipeline

```
Raw Inputs → Elicitation Document → Epics → User Stories → SRS → Test Cases
               ↑ review gate        ↑ gate   ↑ gate       ↑ gate   ↑ gate
```

| Phase | Skill | Artifact | Status |
|-------|-------|----------|--------|
| 1 | `/elicit` | Elicitation Document | Pending |
| 2 | `/create-epics` | Epics | Pending |
| 3 | `/create-stories` | User Stories | Pending |
| 4 | `/create-srs` | Software Requirements Specification | Pending |
| 5 | `/create-tests` | Test Concept + Test Cases | Pending |
| 6 | `/trace` | Traceability Matrix | Pending |

## How to Use

**Start a new phase:**
1. Drop input documents into `inputs/`
2. Claude Code: run `/elicit` — GitHub Copilot: "Run the elicit skill"
3. Review the generated artifact
4. Type `APPROVED` to proceed to the next phase

**Update with new inputs:**
Run `/elicit` again after adding new documents. The skill detects new inputs automatically via `inputs/manifest.md`.

